    <p>Base64 isn't complicated once you see past the ugly strings. It's just a straightforward conversion — 3 bytes in, 4 characters out — designed to make binary data safe for text-based systems. The next time you encounter a Base64 string, you'll know exactly what you're looking at and what to do with it.</p>

